                  </hi>. I keep a shop in Ludgate-street. About eight o'clock, on the 17th August, I had 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. of silver in my till—I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner, who is my porter, walk round the counter, open the till, and take two half-crowns and seven shillings out—I called in a policeman, gave him in charge, and found the money on him—he had no business at the till.</p>
